      1. Using `with` keyword — WRONG: `tool scaffold with` / RIGHT: `tool scaffold`
      2. Using curly braces — WRONG: `workflow X { }` / RIGHT: indentation only
      3. Using parentheses — WRONG: `parallel X (` / RIGHT: `parallel X -> A, B`
      4. Using brackets in edges — WRONG: `A -> B [when x = 1]` / RIGHT: `A -> B  when x = 1`
